<br>
  1)  It is a _log.txt and notes.txt parser.<br>
  2)  It runs while the game is running watching these files.<br>
  3)  Based on configurable settings the user provides via /note commands in-game, it provides feedback via the microsoft text-to-speech engine.  Namely, creating a timer, watching for a keyword in a log file, and gathering damage stats.<br>
  4)  Users can create 'timers' which fire after a given period of time (that they provide - I've have been asked to keep a database of spawn timers which I have declined as right now it kind of forces the user to already know when a spawn/spell is about to fire - ie - requires a brain)<br>
  5)  Users can get damage feedback from the log files.  ala &quot;You did 500 points of damage at 10 points per second&quot;.<br>
<br>
  Things I would like you to assess would be:<br>
<br>
  a)  Does it violate the EULA (in my best approximation &quot;no&quot;)<br>
  b)  If so, does everything it does violate? or if some pieces can remain -- you tell me which please.<br>
<br>
  c)  If there is some violation, pity on my character, as I am writing to you in full faith of this discussion being &quot;above-board&quot; to actually get constructive feedback.  Should your findings say the whole thing violates the EULA - I will shut it down promptly.<br>
